CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 17, 1966, pg. 4B reads: "Ohio Quintet - This group from Youngstown, Ohio were part of the gay crowd enjoying the smart dinner-dance given by the Junior Mothers Club during the Labor Day weekend. Held at the Flying Carpet, music was provided by Bobby Jones and his organ quartet.  Seat[ed] from left: Mrs. Nathaniel Jones and Mrs. B.R. McDuffie.  Standing from left: Dr. James Franklin, Atty. Nathaniel Jones and Dr. B.R. McDuffie. (Harris photo)."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three men and two women, seated left to right; Mrs. Nathaniel Jones and Mrs. B.R. McDuffie, standing left to right; Dr. Jones Franklin, Nathaniel Jones, and Dr. B.R. McDuffie, gathered around bench in the Flying Carpet Motel
